00:19:37.590 --> 00:19:41.010
from these lesions,
particularly when Staph aureus

00:19:41.010 --> 00:19:44.650
or another bacteria
begins an infection.

00:19:44.650 --> 00:19:47.920
And especially for people
who have been displaced,

00:19:47.920 --> 00:19:50.410
people living in refugee camps

00:19:50.410 --> 00:19:54.310
without adequate access
to medical care.

00:19:54.310 --> 00:19:58.930
And once these lesions heal,
they often cause scarring,

00:19:58.930 --> 00:20:02.270
pretty significant
scarring on the face,

00:20:02.270 --> 00:20:05.360
and that can lead to social stigma.

00:20:05.360 --> 00:20:09.580
It can lead to bullying and
depression, a loss of education

00:20:09.580 --> 00:20:13.220
if children then don't want to
go to school and in some parts

00:20:13.220 --> 00:20:15.450
of the world for young girls,

00:20:15.450 --> 00:20:19.110
it can lead to a loss
of marriage prospects.

00:20:19.110 --> 00:20:22.940
So if you contract this and
you live in a part of the world

00:20:22.940 --> 00:20:27.350
with stable access to medical
care, you could receive treatment

00:20:27.350 --> 00:20:31.420
by cryotherapy or thermal therapy.

00:20:31.420 --> 00:20:37.470
But typically the drug most usually
used is called pentastem [ph],

00:20:37.470 --> 00:20:43.580
and this is injected either
intramuscularly or intralesionally.

00:20:43.580 --> 00:20:48.590
And depending on the
type of species,

00:20:48.590 --> 00:20:51.650
Leishmaniasis species
causing the problem,

00:20:51.650 --> 00:20:56.080
the treatment can be quite
painful, quite long up to 18 months

00:20:56.080 --> 00:20:58.310
in duration for some people.

00:20:58.310 --> 00:21:04.450 position:56%
And you can imagine this is quite a
disheartening prospect for patients.

00:21:04.450 --> 00:21:07.570
Some people will refuse
the injections and try

00:21:07.570 --> 00:21:11.630
and treat it themselves by
burning the lesions with cigarettes

00:21:11.630 --> 00:21:14.840
or with fire, trying
to cut the lesion,

00:21:14.840 --> 00:21:18.430
which clearly is not going
to help the situation.

00:21:18.430 --> 00:21:25.490
So what does this have
to do with eyesalve?

00:21:26.990 --> 00:21:36.100
In the assay shown here, live
parasites were exposed to dilutions

00:21:36.100 --> 00:21:38.570
of both versions of the eyesalve.

00:21:38.570 --> 00:21:42.790
Both onion and leek
over a two day period.

00:21:42.790 --> 00:21:47.870
After the two day period,
a dye was added in order

00:21:47.870 --> 00:21:51.970
to measure metabolic
activity to measure

00:21:51.970 --> 00:21:55.530
if the parasites are alive or dead.

00:21:55.530 --> 00:22:01.380
When parasites are alive,
the dye turns bright pink.

00:22:01.380 --> 00:22:06.060
When parasites are dead,
the dye stays dark blue.

00:22:06.060 --> 00:22:08.840
And you can see where
it says onion variant

00:22:08.840 --> 00:22:12.810
and leek variant the
dye is dark blue.

00:22:12.810 --> 00:22:16.740
It's clearly dead parasites.

00:22:16.740 --> 00:22:20.750
Now, this is quite
an exciting result

00:22:20.750 --> 00:22:23.910
but it's also a preliminary result.

00:22:23.910 --> 00:22:29.590
Right now the eyesalve is being
tested on human macrophage cells

00:22:29.590 --> 00:22:34.760
in order to ascertain its
effects on human cells.

00:22:34.760 --> 00:22:43.450
So it has to be determined that the
eyesalve is harmless to human cells

00:22:43.450 --> 00:22:50.050
but maintains its toxicity against
the parasites living within them.

00:22:50.050 --> 00:22:57.040
To summarize this evidence, but I
went through a little bit quickly,

00:22:57.040 --> 00:23:01.750 position:56%
all of the ingredients are necessary
for the eyesalve to work except

00:23:01.750 --> 00:23:06.180
