00:32:01.920 --> 00:32:06.720
on the great virtue
of interdisciplinary

00:32:06.720 --> 00:32:10.270
and international collaboration.

00:32:10.270 --> 00:32:14.930
The arts and sciences
are often presented

00:32:14.930 --> 00:32:17.560
as these diametric opposites.

00:32:17.560 --> 00:32:24.570
But hopefully, in this talk I've
shown how much we need each other

00:32:24.570 --> 00:32:31.160 position:56%
and that when we work together we
can produce results that are greater

00:32:31.160 --> 00:32:33.800
than the sum of our
individual parts.

00:32:33.800 --> 00:32:38.660
And clearly not every
collaboration is created equally.

00:32:38.660 --> 00:32:43.940
And it requires very
specific traits to be part

00:32:43.940 --> 00:32:49.010
of such a well integrated
and unified team.

00:32:49.010 --> 00:32:51.560
Turning historical medical text

00:32:51.560 --> 00:32:58.180
